CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 7, 1951, pg. 3, reads: "Chairs Conference - Elected as chairman of the 1951 Bethany Conference of the YWCA, after going to last year's confab as a delegate of the Pepperettes, Lyda Jo Boswell, daughter of Mr. and Mrs. John M. Boswell, daughter of Mr. and Mrs. John M. Boswell, poses with 'Susie,' the mascot of the meeting. As chairman, she met with five different teen-age groups during the past year and presided over most of the sessions of the recent get-together.  She attends Schenley High School."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Lyda Jo Boswell holding Pepperettes paper doll mascot "Susie," in Harris Studio
